name: Lilaga
product_desc:
With very high rate of urbanisation, Malawi has not provided the housing needed and there is shortage of housing. Mortgage finance is not an option for the majority hence incremental construction by all income groups. Lilaga is providing plots for households to start their home ownership journey. Lilaga consolidates land, plans, services and sells the plots on the market.

Lilaga begun consolidating land and developing plots and putting them on the market this year. To date 400 plots have been sold since April 2016 and the demand keeps growing. The high rate of urbanisation and lack of plots on the market makes our products attractive. The ease with which Lilaga is able to assemble land and demarcate at the pace that brings very high value for money. The payment mechanisms makes the products attractive.

To start with we are focusing on Lilongwe, but we have to reach to other parts of Malawi and eventually SubSaharan Africa. Most of our clients are first time home owners and investors
high_concept: Investment Platform for African Real Estate DEVELOPMENT
markets: Investment Management, Crowdfunding, Real Estate Investors, Urban Development

name: Face of Hope, Malawi
product_desc:
Face of Hope is a non-profit organisation that aims to conduct activities that would provide protection and support for victims and potential victims of child abuse and domestic violence. 
The organisation aims to provide services and help with policies that would identify, protect, support and empower victims of domestic violence and child abuse.
Face of Hope will also work to prevent incidences of child abuse and domestic violence by attempting to alter cultural and social standards in Malawi
high_concept: Support for victims of child abuse and domestic violence

name: Noble Creations
product_desc: Noble Creations (Noble) is an organisation run on Christian principals with the aim of bringing change and growing an artistic generation in Africa. Noble is here to bring opportunities to young creators to create and express themselves through the arts. Our aim is to set up creative houses on wide bases; so they will be accessible to as many young people as possible. Noble also aims to start workshops in schools to give people opportunities to see their personal abilities, during the workshops Noble will teach students the importance of art and what effect it has on our current economy. Noble intends to attract a minimum of 120 young people every month per centre. Noble is also aiming to hold workshops at a minimum of 2 schools a month; we will spend 3 days at each school.
high_concept: When Creating, The Sky Is The Limit.

name: RECAPO Solar Systems
product_desc:
Pay as You Go Solar leasing for rural households in Malawi. RECAPO has partnered with Azuri Technologies Ltd to supply the Indigo Solar Systems in Malawi.
A typical rural household in Malawi spends $13.50/month on candles, kerosene burners and charging cell phones at trading centers. The Indigo Solar Home System comes with two LED lights and an outlet for charging cell phones at price that saves a household more than $5.20/month when they switch to Indigo.
A household pays an initial installation fee and purchases weekly activation cards for a period up to 80 weeks. This is leasing and finance facility never heard in these communities commonly referred to as unbankable for conventional banking systems.
A limited number of systems were leased out in Chimutu are, Lilongwe, Malawi in March 2014,  we have achieved a 100% weekly activation purchases, ZERO defaults! This is truly low risk investing whilst doing a lot of good!
status: RECAPO, engaging in rural electrification in Malawi is now on Angelist
